<HEADLINE>
FT  23 NOV 94 / Letters to the Editor (3): Well paid, well equipped and
subject to market forces
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr ROLAND DAVIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Since the market rate for a chief executive of multinational calibre is
Pounds 475,000, I hope British Gas will go to the market and find such a
person, instead of retaining its present chief executive who, according to
market forces, is worth only Pounds 270,000.
Roland Davis,
Wayside House, High Street,
Shoreham, Kent
</TEXT>
