<HEADLINE>
FT  22 NOV 94 / Schools' League Tables: Terminology
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A-LEVEL: Advanced Level General Certificate of Education, the main
examination for university entrance in England and Wales.
UCAS POINTS: Based on ratings of A-levels by the Universities and Colleges
Admissions Service, awarding 10 points for an A grade at A level, 8 for a B,
and so on.
GCSE: General Certificate of Secondary Education, taken by 16-year-olds in
England and Wales. A grade C is equivalent to an old O-level pass.
</TEXT>
