<HEADLINE>
FT  22 NOV 94 / World Trade News: Kumagi Gumi and Cubiertas y Mzov and
Entrecanales - Contracts &amp; ventures
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A consortium, consisting of Kumagai Gumi of Japan and Cubiertas y Mzov and
Entrecanales, both of Spain, has been awarded a HKDollars 2.6bn (Dollars
336.3m) civil engineering contract to build an underground railway station
in Kowloon, part of the 34km rail link to Hong Kong's new HKDollars 158bn
airport complex, Mass Transit Railway (MTRC) announced. MTRC also said that
a German-Spanish consortium, consisting of AEG Aktiengesellschaft and CAF,
had been awarded a HKDollars 1.6bn rolling stock contract to build 11
express and 12 ordinary trains for the airport link. Thirty-one large
contracts are expected to be awarded by MTRC, which is responsible for
building the rail link.
