<HEADLINE>
FT  22 NOV 94 / Rise in Japanese household spending
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By GERARD BAKER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Japan's household spending in the three months to September rose by 0.5 per
cent in real terms from the same period a year before, according to figures
published yesterday by the Management and Co-ordination Agency, Gerard Baker
reports. The increase was the first in three quarters, and suggests the
gradual economic recovery is lifting consumption. Household spending in the
month of September alone increased 2.0 per cent from a year earlier,
following a 0.4 per cent fall in August, a 0.1 per cent rise in July, and
five consecutive monthly falls to June. Agency officials said the increase
was largely due to special income tax cuts which took effect in the summer.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>JPZ  Japan, Asia.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P9311 Finance, Taxation, and Monetary Policy.
</IN>
<XX>
