<HEADLINE>
FT  22 NOV 94 / EU urged to push green issues
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HILARY BARNES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COPENHAGEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Environmental policies should become an integrated part of all European
Union policies, including agriculture, energy, transport, industry, regional
and structural policies and relations with east Europe, says the EU's
incoming commissioner for the environment, Ms Ritt Bjerregaard, a Danish
Social Democrat. 'My opinion is that it could and will have negative
consequences for the environment if the environment is not taken into
consideration when we are discussing all these other areas,' she said
yesterday.
She sees environmental policy as a way for the EU to respond more to public
opinion and therefore to make the EU more popular.
'I think there are in general high expectations from the citizens of Europe.
The environment is one of the very big issues in which a lot of people all
over Europe are interested, and I shall try to meet these expectations,'
said Ms Bjerregaard.
</TEXT>
