<HEADLINE>
FT  21 NOV 94 / Company News (This Week): Tokyo Electric Power - Other
companies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The world's largest electric power company is expected to announce a small
fall in recurring profits on Tuesday, from Y58.5bn to Y58bn, despite the
summer heatwave. Kansai Electric Power, the world's second-largest power
group, will report better results on the same day. Analysts expect Kansai's
interim profits to rise from Y49bn to Y65bn.
